The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Tuesday, March 09, 2004 				 Celebrating modern arts
																								In an effort to bring about a renaissance in the field of alternative arts in Calcutta, Sapphire Creations Dance Workshop presents Interface 2004, an international festival of the visual and performing arts. Covering music, dance, theatre, photography, puppetry and fashion, this biennial festival celebrates the avant-garde, encouraging an alternative strain of thought and performance, and at the same time creating a platform for the interaction and reinvention of the contemporary arts. The festival begins today with Dance Expressions, a performance by Astad Deboo. Having worked with both ancient classical forms and experimental modern dance styles, Deboo is a master of a variety of dance traditions and techniques, with a unique style that radiates a rare blend of cerebral intensity and artistic exuberance. Interface 2004 will also see outstanding performances by various Indian and international dance troupes, including Thresh Dance Company of the US, Silesian Dance Theatre of Poland and Y-Space Dance Company of Hong Kong, to name a few.																								Event: International Festival of Alternative and Contemporary Expressions																								When: Till March 13; 6.30 pm																								Where: Kala Mandir (March 9 -12) and Swabhumi (March 13)
